data.meta_description: A collection of assembled film footage of Warren G. Hardingâ€™s 1923 Western trip. These films feature his stops in Washington, Alaska and Canada and include some of the last film footage taken of the President. Harding arrives in Seattle aboard the U. S. S. Henderson and gives a speech. In Alaska he visits Child's Glacier, drives a "golden spike" on a new government railroad, having stopped for a meal in Curry and to see a large elk herd in Cantwell. President Harding is warmly greeted in Vancouver.
